Whenever he is alone, he paints his own World in his dreams.
He tries to save atleast the tear that rolls down his cheeks helplessly.
And he recollects those colours in the morning on his pillow!
Despite his average life, he is still a slave to his  brooding past.
With broken heart and teary eyes, he forgot what love is nor does he holds anyone's hands firmly.
For every hand he held, it ripped and tore his soul apart!
They used his affection to get out of their own troubles, leaving him alone!
Fearing all the angelic faces that taught him a lesson, he is waiting for someone with no mask to put his broken soul together.
He waits for a TRUE friend atleast, to save him from this hell!
.
.
.

